Ukraine Harvested 30 Million Tons of Grains, Ministry Says

-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a   a n d   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-08-01T14:17:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/ukraine-harvested-30-million-tons-of-grains-ministry-says-1-.html
Ukrainian farmers harvested 30
million metric tons of grain from 10.1 million hectares (24.95
million acres) as of today, the  Agriculture Ministry  said.  Wheat, reaped from 6.1 million hectares, accounted for 20.5
million tons and barley for 8.5 million tons, the Kiev-based
ministry said in an e-mailed statement. Average yields increased
for wheat to 3.4 tons a hectare from 2.8 tons last year. Barley
yields increased to 2.5 tons a hectare from 2.1 tons.  Farmers reaped 1.3 million tons of rapeseed from 759,000
hectares and rapeseed yields were unchanged from last year at
1.6 tons a hectare, the ministry said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net ;
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
